### HMS Clinical Service API Collection
### Port: 3002 | Base URL: http://localhost:3002
### Auth: Bearer token via Keycloak

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3002
@keycloakUrl = http://localhost:8080
@realm = hms
@clientId = hms-backend
@clientSecret = your-client-secret
@doctorId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@doctorName = Dr. Jenny Smith

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 0. GET ACCESS TOKEN
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 0. Get Access Token (Keycloak)
# @name getToken
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&client_secret={{clientSecret}}&username=admin&password=admin

### Auth token (auto-filled after step 0)
@adminToken = {{getToken.response.body.access_token}}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SESSIONS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Create a new clinical session
# @name createClinicalSession
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "sessionType": "opd",
  "chiefComplaint": "Persistent fever for 3 days"
}

###

@sessionId = {{createClinicalSession.response.body.data.id}}
@patientId = {{createClinicalSession.response.body.data.patientId}}

### 2. List sessions
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

### 3. Get session by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

### 4. Update session
PUT {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chiefComplaint": "Updated complaint",
  "diagnosis": "Suspected Typhoid"
}

###

### 5. Complete session
PUT {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "diagnosis": "Typhoid Fever — Widal test positive",
  "discountPercent": 0
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITALS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6. Record vitals
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/vitals
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bpm": 80,
  "temperature": 37.8,
  "bloodPressureSys": 120,
  "bloodPressureDia": 80,
  "spo2": 98,
  "weightKg": 68.5,
  "heightCm": 170
}

###

### 7. Get vitals
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/vitals
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

### 8. Get vitals history for patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}/vitals-history
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRESCRIPTIONS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 9. Add prescriptions
# @name addPrescriptions
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/prescriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prescriptions": [
    {
      "type": "internal",
      "medicineName": "Paracetamol",
      "dosage": "500mg",
      "frequency": "Every 8 hours",
      "durationDays": 5,
      "instructions": "Take with water after meals"
    },
    {
      "type": "external",
      "medicineName": "Amoxicillin",
      "dosage": "500mg",
      "frequency": "Three times daily",
      "durationDays": 7,
      "pharmacyName": "Narammala Pharmacy"
    }
  ]
}

###

### 10. Get session prescriptions
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/prescriptions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

### 11. Get session prescriptions by type
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/prescriptions?type=internal
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHARMACY
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: pharmacy queue only shows prescriptions from COMPLETED sessions.
# Prescriptions from open/ongoing sessions are hidden until the doctor completes the session.
#
# NATS event: pharmacy.new_rx  (published by clinical-service → PHARMACY JetStream stream)
# Triggered: when PUT /sessions/{id}/complete is called AND the session has ≥1 internal prescription
# Payload:
#   {
#     "sessionId": "<uuid>",
#     "patientId": "<uuid>",
#     "patientName": "string",
#     "doctorName": "string",
#     "completedAt": "2026-03-02T09:00:00",
#     "prescriptions": [
#       { "id": "<uuid>", "medicineName": "Paracetamol", "dosage": "500mg",
#         "frequency": "Every 8 hours", "durationDays": 5, "instructions": "Take with water" }
#     ]
#   }
# Intended consumer: WebSocket gateway → Pharmacy Display (real-time notification)

### 12. Get pharmacy queue (only completed-session pending internal prescriptions)
GET {{baseUrl}}/pharmacy/queue
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

# Prescription ID — update manually based on the queue details
@rxId = 9f8b077d-92c7-4a5e-8660-94b323b20cf6

### 13. Dispense prescription
PUT {{baseUrl}}/pharmacy/{{rxId}}/dispense
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LAB REQUESTS
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 14. Request lab tests
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/lab-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tests": [
    { "testId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001", "urgency": "routine" },
    { "testId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002", "urgency": "urgent" }
  ],
  "notes": "Patient has fever for 3 days — suspect typhoid"
}

###

### 15. Get lab requests
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/lab-requests
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PATIENT HISTORY
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 16. Get patient clinical history
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}/history?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMAGES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 17. Upload image (multipart)
# Use Postman or cURL:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3002/sessions/{{sessionId}}/images \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
#   -F "image=@path/to/image.jpg" \
#   -F "caption=Left knee X-ray" \
#   -F "imageType=scan"

###

### 18. Get session images
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/images
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
X-User-Id: {{doctorId}}
X-User-Name: {{doctorName}}

###
